‖   § Definition ⦉⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ An ❬orthonormal❭ (or ❬orthogonal❭) matrix is a matrix whose
    columns are an orthonormal family of vectors. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ Some authors call these ❬real orthogonal❭ or ❬unitary❭
    matrices. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $A ∈ 𝗙^{m × n}$. ⦉

  ‖ Something something
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ AA^⊤ = I. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§ Characterizations ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ A matrix is orthonormal if and only if its transpose
    product with the matrix is the identity. ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ A matrix is orthonormal if and only if its transpose is
    orthonormal. ⦉
</statement>
